title: Council Effluent Lead at Site
metadata_json: {"compliance_id": "7858c14c-bc25-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Site Updates/Notifications", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/LicenseeReturns/byid?lr_id=7858c14c-bc25-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "title": "Council Effluent Lead at Site", "description": "On Friday, April 25th, at approximately 12:44 PM, it was observed that the Uisce \u00c9ireann town effluent tank at the Portumna Pastry site was overflowing. Raw sewage was observed entering both the site's stormwater network and directly flowing into the nearby stream, which feeds into Lough Derg. Local council operatives were promptly notified, and they addressed the issue by activating the diesel generator pump onsite, owned by Uisce \u00c9ireann.\r\n\r\nUisce \u00c9ireann pumps the effluent across the site to the local effluent treatment plant. Originally installed as a temporary measure in 2015, this system remains in use today. However, the permanently temporary pipe transporting effluent is currently leaking into the nearby stream, which eventually flows into Lough Derg.", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{\"licenseereturnid\": \"7858c14c-bc25-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a\", \"type\": \"Site Updates/Notifications\", \"reference\": \"LR094063\", \"subject\": \"Site Updates/Notifications:Other\", \"status\": \"Closed\", \"licenceid\": \"26c8e87d-7c61-e211-9eb5-0050568a69e2\", \"licenceprofileid\": \"8eef72b4-227d-4e72-b0af-37e8f03d898e\", \"datereceived\": \"2025-04-30T00:00:00\", \"closeddate\": \"2025-05-22T00:00:00\", \"title\": \"Council Effluent Lead at Site\", \"doctype\": \"Site Updates/Notifications\", \"docsubtype\": \"Other\", \"decision\": \"Assessed\", \"description\": \"On Friday, April 25th, at approximately 12:44 PM, it was observed that the Uisce \\u00c9ireann town effluent tank at the Portumna Pastry site was overflowing. Raw sewage was observed entering both the site's stormwater network and directly flowing into the nearby stream, which feeds into Lough Derg. Local council operatives were promptly notified, and they addressed the issue by activating the diesel generator pump onsite, owned by Uisce \\u00c9ireann.\\r\\n\\r\\nUisce \\u00c9ireann pumps the effluent across the site to the local effluent treatment plant. Originally installed as a temporary measure in 2015, this system remains in use today. However, the permanently temporary pipe transporting effluent is currently leaking into the nearby stream, which eventually flows into Lough Derg.\", \"documentcategory\": null, \"complianceinvestigationid\": null}"}

title: Response to LR Rejection issued on the 29/04/2025
metadata_json:
{"compliance_id": "d7d4ba45-c425-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Annual Environmental Report", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/LicenseeReturns/byid?lr_id=d7d4ba45-c425-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "title": "Response to LR Rejection issued on the 29/04/2025", "description": "Dear Cyrina

I refer to your one way notification with a license return rejection notice issued on the 29/04/2025 in relation to the 2024 AER.I note you refer to the EDEN notification issued to licensed sites on the 20/02/2025 setting out new guidance but on the back of that the IFA Pig & Poultry Policy executive engaged with the EPA following concerns raised by several consultants around the EMP and an email was issued to the IFA on the 6/03/2025 (Attached) by the EPA which clearly states that any sites of whom were issued with a Technical amendment during 2024 were not required to have the EMP and therefore environmental objectives and targets implemented as these requirements were not applicable.

This facility was only issued the TA on the 21/5/2024 so hence why no EMP (objective and targets) were provided for 2024 reporting based on the attached email from the EPA. This is the same for the other two Fenor Pig Farms Ltd facilities. A full EMS is in place for this site and environmental Objectives and targets will be reported for the 2025 AER.

Regards
David  ", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{"licenseereturnid": "d7d4ba45-c425-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "type": "Annual Environmental Report", "reference": "LR094070", "subject": "Annual Environmental Report:AER", "status": "Closed", "licenceid": "bec7e87d-7c61-e211-9eb5-0050568a69e2", "licenceprofileid": "2f28547d-3a6e-43f3-8627-db041de89cdc", "datereceived": "2025-04-30T00:00:00", "closeddate": "2025-05-21T00:00:00", "title": "Response to LR Rejection issued on the 29/04/2025", "doctype": "Annual Environmental Report", "docsubtype": "AER", "decision": "Assessed", "description": "Dear Cyrina\r\n\r\nI refer to your one way notification with a license return rejection notice issued on the 29/04/2025 in relation to the 2024 AER.I note you refer to the EDEN notification issued to licensed sites on the 20/02/2025 setting out new guidance but on the back of that the IFA Pig & Poultry Policy executive engaged with the EPA following concerns raised by several consultants around the EMP and an email was issued to the IFA on the 6/03/2025 (Attached) by the EPA which clearly states that any sites of whom were issued with a Technical amendment during 2024 were not required to have the EMP and therefore environmental objectives and targets implemented as these requirements were not applicable.\r\n\r\nThis facility was only issued the TA on the 21/5/2024 so hence why no EMP (objective and targets) were provided for 2024 reporting based on the attached email from the EPA. This is the same for the other two Fenor Pig Farms Ltd facilities. A full EMS is in place for this site and environmental Objectives and targets will be reported for the 2025 AER.\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nDavid  ", "documentcategory": null, "complianceinvestigationid": null}"}

metadata_json:

Please be advised that SE1 Composite sampler will be offline for a period of time today (up to half a day) to facilitate the electrical installation of a breaker in the SE1 sampling kiosk. This work is being carried out to facilitate the power installation of a second composite sampler for redundancy. 

Please note, there will be no waste water discharged during the time that the sampler is offline. Continuous monitoring will resume once works are completed and discharge has recommenced. 

Should you have any queries, please do not hesitate to contact me.

Kind Regards,
Emily Holland

The result was 4.1 mg/l. The ELV limit is 2 mg/l and the max. limit is 2.4 mg/l. Investigations into the operations at the WWtP have confirmed there were no operational issues to note at the plant with SCADA trends checked and DO levels, cones and flows all noted as been within normal levels at present and at the time of the exceedance. A final effluent process sample (unaccredited) taken on the 28/04/2025 yielded a compliant ammonia result of 0.24 mg/l. MLSS levels also measured on the 28/04/2025 were recorded as 1,600 mg/l, with wasting levels increased on site on the 28/04/2025 to increase MLSS levels. Operations at the plant to be kept under review with further MLSS monitoring to continue. Once available, a further update will be provided. Srowland WTP and Kildare Co Co Environment Section were notified of this ELV breach on the 28/04/2025 @13:50.

title: Activated sludge control programme works
metadata_json:
{"compliance_id": "4352d7b6-b325-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Site Updates/Notifications", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/LicenseeReturns/byid?lr_id=4352d7b6-b325-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "title": "Activated sludge control programme works", "description": "Contractors are to commence automation works for the Activated Sludge Control Programme at Mountmellick WWTP on 06/05/2025, with works to begin as follows: 
Replacement of the existing Siemens PLC and HMI with a new I/O distribution unit and integration of the existing control functionality from the Siemens PLC to the Unitronics PLC.
Provision of new controls for the Oxidation Ditch flow boosters.
Provision of additional CPU and small control panel for the WAS pumps in the sludge dewatering building.
Works expected to be complete by start Q3 2025.
", "submission_date": "", "status": "Open", "metadata": "{"licenseereturnid": "4352d7b6-b325-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "type": "Site Updates/Notifications", "reference": "LR094057", "subject": "Site Updates/Notifications:Infrastructure Update", "status": "Open", "licenceid": "de2076ab-203e-e111-ab87-0050568a69e2", "licenceprofileid": "ba42cb56-2087-422b-94fa-522a5b872952", "datereceived": "2025-04-30T00:00:00", "closeddate": null, "title": "Activated sludge control programme works", "doctype": "Site Updates/Notifications", "docsubtype": "Infrastructure Update", "decision": null, "description": "Contractors are to commence automation works for the Activated Sludge Control Programme at Mountmellick WWTP on 06/05/2025, with works to begin as follows: \r\nReplacement of the existing Siemens PLC and HMI with a new I/O distribution unit and integration of the existing control functionality from the Siemens PLC to the Unitronics PLC.\r\nProvision of new controls for the Oxidation Ditch flow boosters.\r\nProvision of additional CPU and small control panel for the WAS pumps in the sludge dewatering building.\r\nWorks expected to be complete by start Q3 2025.\r\n", "documentcategory": null, "complianceinvestigationid": null}"}

{"compliance_id": "bddadfda-c25e-44f9-b357-5c6410984fb3", "document_type": "Meeting", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/MeetingCorrespondence/meetingbyid?meeting_id=bddadfda-c25e-44f9-b357-5c6410984fb3", "title": "", "description": "", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{\"meetingid\": \"bddadfda-c25e-44f9-b357-5c6410984fb3\", \"type\": \"Meeting\", \"reference\": \"MTG000746\", \"subject\": \"Ringsend WWTP upgrade project update from Uisce \\u00c9ireann\", \"status\": \"Closed\", \"meetingdate\": \"2025-04-07T00:00:00\", \"organisationid\": \"f5545f77-3749-e211-9eb5-0050568a69e2\", \"location\": \"Online MS Teams\", \"regarding\": \"Compliance Investigations\", \"meetingtime\": \"12:00\", \"attendeesepa\": \"Lorcan Farrell, Stephen McCarthy, David Shannon\", \"attendeesnoepa\": \"Uisce \\u00c9ireann: Ringsend WWTP Upgrade Project Team, Compliance Team & Asset Operations\\n\", \"actionitems\": \"

A video conference meeting was held between the EPA and Uisce Éireann (UÉ) on 08/04/2025 from 12:00 to 12:50 approx.

\\n

During the meeting UÉ gave an update to the EPA on the phased upgrades being undertaken at Ringsend WWTP and a summary of treatment plant performance for Q1 2025.

\\n

Works on Hybrid II upgrades and sludge treatment facilities are progressing as scheduled with all primary aspects of the upgrade project due for completion by end 2025. A programme of ancillary works connected with the overall upgrade project is also being progressed with most completion dates falling within 2025.

\\n

A summary of plant performance was given. UÉ are aiming for 104 compliance samples to be taken during 2025. 10 no. samples records were recorded in the Q1 Update under compliance investigation (CI000025).  Compliance results were unavailable for the first three weeks of January. This was attributed to operational reasons (plant shutdowns) and management changeover. It is UÉ’s intention to make up the shortfall to 104 compliance samples over the year. It was acknowledged that there is a risk that TN and TP average limits may not be achieved this year. UÉ expect that performance will improve across all parameters once remaining upgraded SBR blocks come back on-line and as average air temperatures increase through the year. UÉ confirmed that higher than expected load on the plant (2.17 PE in 2024) was expected to continue increasing in 2025 and is also affecting treatment performance. Issues with the aeration system in the Capital Upgrade treatment block were also cited as a compounding factor in treatment performance and should be resolved by end April 2025.

\\n

The EPA instructed Uisce Éireann to carry out all actions necessary to comply with the waste water discharge licence.

\", \"licenceid\": \"4ab24fc5-2bf8-4aa8-ad9e-f4f68c559186\", \"originalmeetingid\": \"0d83b2ed-7614-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a\", \"organisationname\": \"Uisce \\u00c9ireann\"}"}

{"compliance_id": "8d246f0c-35f7-4d1c-b1bc-b24469edd2a7", "document_type": "Meeting", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/MeetingCorrespondence/meetingbyid?meeting_id=8d246f0c-35f7-4d1c-b1bc-b24469edd2a7", "title": "", "description": "", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{\"meetingid\": \"8d246f0c-35f7-4d1c-b1bc-b24469edd2a7\", \"type\": \"Meeting\", \"reference\": \"MTG000742\", \"subject\": \"P0801-03: Tipperary Co-Op Compliance Meeting\", \"status\": \"Closed\", \"meetingdate\": \"2025-03-06T00:00:00\", \"organisationid\": \"5c83ffb3-458d-e111-ab87-0050568a69e2\", \"location\": \"Tipperary Co-Op Site\", \"regarding\": \"Compliance Investigations\", \"meetingtime\": \"11:00\", \"attendeesepa\": \"Pamela McDonald - Programme Manager \\nIrene Doyle - Senior Inspector \\nBilly Shanahan - Inspector \", \"attendeesnoepa\": \"John Hunter - Tipperary Co-Op Site Manager \\nSe\\u00e1n Hennebry - Tipperary Co-Op EHS Graduate\\nTony Motherway - Tipperary Co-Op Engineer \\nKevin Sheehan - Consultant \\nPeadar O'Loughlin - Consultant \\nJason McAndrew - Arrabawn Project Manager \\nShane Mulcahy - Arrabawn Maintenance Manager \", \"actionitems\": \"

A discussion was held regarding the outstanding issues on site and the proposed timeframes on addressing these issues.

\\n

Tipperary Co-Op site manager gave an update on the merger with Arrabawn being completed and that there would be a new structure confirmed in the next couple of weeks. This new structure will be submitted to the EPA upon finalisation.

\\n

The site manager handed over to their consultant to give a presentation on the site history, the projects undertaken in conjunction with the EPA licence and the actions to be undertaken to resolve the historical compliance issues and projects to improve site efficiency.

\\n

The Programme Manager then spoke about the length of time given to the licensee to date to address issues on site and that the site has been on the EPA’s National Priority Sites list since 2021 and the ongoing legal action taken by the EPA. The licensee was instructed to give a letter of commitment that all issues outstanding will be addressed. This letter is to be signed by the licensee’s Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Chairperson and Treasurer. The letter is to be submitted by Licensee Returns on EDEN within 2 weeks.

\\n

The Programme Manager also expressed their concern of the risk the site poses to the River Ara, that they are a significant pressure on the waterbody achieving good status by 2027. Furthermore, the Programme Manager indicated that they intend on visiting the site again should matters not improve.        

\\n

A site inspection followed and is detailed in Site Visit Ref. No. SV32398.
